{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"role":"article","title":"Adopting Common Protocols"},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/adopting-common-protocols"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Make your custom types easier to use by ensuring that they conform to Swift protocols."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Data Modeling","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/choosing-between-structures-and-classes"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Data-Modeling"}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using custom types to model data in your programs, you may frequently need to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"check whether two values are the same or different, or whether a particular value"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is included in a list of values. This capability, as well as the ability to store"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values in a set or use them as keys in a dictionary, are governed by two related"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"standard library protocols, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can compare instances of an "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"equatable"}]},{"type":"text","text":" type by using the equal-to ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":") and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not-equal-to ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"!="},{"text":") operators.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An instance of a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hashable"}]},{"text":" type can reduce its value mathematically to a single","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"integer, which is used internally by sets and dictionaries to make lookups consistently","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fast.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Many standard library types are both equatable and hashable, including strings, integers,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"floating-point values, Boolean values, and collections of equatable and hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":" comparison and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"contains(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method call in the following example"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"depend on strings and integers being equatable:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["if username == \"Arturo\" {","    print(\"Hi, Arturo!\")","}","","let favoriteNumbers = [4, 7, 8, 9]","if favoriteNumbers.contains(todaysDate.day) {","    print(\"It's a good day today!\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Conforming to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" protocols is straightforward and makes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it easier to use your own types in Swift. It’s a good idea for all your custom model"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"types to conform."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Conform Automatically to Equatable and Hashable","anchor":"Conform-Automatically-to-Equatable-and-Hashable"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can make many custom types equatable and hashable by simply declaring these protocol","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conformances in the same file as the type’s original declaration. Add "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to the list of adopted protocols when declaring the type, and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compiler automatically fills in the requirements for the two protocols:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/\/ A position in an x-y coordinate system.","struct Position: Equatable, Hashable {","    var x: Int","    var y: Int","","    init(_ x: Int, _ y: Int) {","        self.x = x","        self.y = y","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With ","type":"text"},{"code":"Equatable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" conformance, you can use the equal-to operator (","type":"text"},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") or the not-equal-to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"operator (","type":"text"},{"code":"!=","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") with any two instances of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Position","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let availablePositions = [Position(0, 0), Position(0, 1), Position(1, 0)]","let gemPosition = Position(1, 0)","","for position in availablePositions {","    if gemPosition == position {","        print(\"Gem found at (\\(position.x), \\(position.y))!\")","    } else {","        print(\"No gem at (\\(position.x), \\(position.y))\")","    }","}","\/\/ No gem at (0, 0)","\/\/ No gem at (0, 1)","\/\/ Gem found at (1, 0)!",""]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" conformance means that you can store positions in a set and quickly check","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether you’ve visited a position before, as shown in the following example:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["var visitedPositions: Set = [Position(0, 0), Position(1, 0)]","let currentPosition = Position(1, 3)","","if visitedPositions.contains(currentPosition) {","    print(\"Already visited (\\(currentPosition.x), \\(currentPosition.y))\")","} else {","    print(\"First time at (\\(currentPosition.x), \\(currentPosition.y))\")","    visitedPositions.insert(currentPosition)","}","\/\/ First time at (1, 3)",""]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In addition to simplifying your code, this automatic conformance reduces errors,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"because any new properties you add to your custom types are automatically included","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"when hashing and testing for equality. A type is eligible for automatic conformance","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to ","type":"text"},{"code":"Equatable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when it’s a structure or an enumeration that meets","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these criteria:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For a structure, ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"all","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" its stored properties must conform to ","type":"text"},{"code":"Equatable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For an enumeration, "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"all"}]},{"type":"text","text":" its associated values must conform to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":". (Enumerations without associated values have "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conformance even without declaring adoption.)"}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Conform-Manually-to-Equatable-and-Hashable","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Conform Manually to Equatable and Hashable"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to manually implement "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" conformance for a type","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in these cases:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The type doesn’t meet the criteria listed in the previous section."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You want to customize the type’s conformance.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You want to extend a type declared in another file or module to conform."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["class Player {","    var name: String","    var position: Position","","    init(name: String, position: Position) {","        self.name = name","        self.position = position","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"Player","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type is a class, so it doesn’t qualify for automatic synthesis of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Equatable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" requirements. To make this class conform to the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Equatable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"protocol, declare conformance in an extension and implement the  static ","type":"text"},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method. Compare each significant property for equality in your ","type":"text"},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method’s implementation:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension Player: Equatable {","    static func ==(lhs: Player, rhs: Player) -> Bool {","        return lhs.name == rhs.name && lhs.position == rhs.position","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To make "},{"code":"Player","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" conform to the "},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol, declare conformance in another"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"extension and implement the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method. In the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"text":" method, call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"combine(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method on the provided hasher with each significant property:"}]},{"code":["extension Player: Hashable {","    func hash(into hasher: inout Hasher) {","        hasher.combine(name)","        hasher.combine(position)","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"text":"Use All Significant Properties for Equatable and Hashable","type":"heading","anchor":"Use-All-Significant-Properties-for-Equatable-and-Hashable"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When implementing the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":" method and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method, use all the properties"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that affect whether two instances of your custom type are considered equal. In the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementations above, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Player"},{"type":"text","text":" type uses "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"position"},{"type":"text","text":" in both methods."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If your type contains properties that don’t affect whether two instances are considered","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"equal, exclude those properties from comparison in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"text":" method and from hashing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"type":"text","text":". For example, a type might cache an expensive computed value so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that it only needs to calculate it once. If you compare two instances of that type,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether or not the computed value has been cached shouldn’t affect their equality,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so the cached value should be excluded from comparison and hashing."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"important","name":"Important","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Always use the same properties in both your ","type":"text"},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"hash(into:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" methods."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Using different groups of properties in the two methods can lead to unexpected behavior"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or performance when using your custom type in sets and dictionaries."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swift\/adopting-common-protocols"]}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"type":"topic","title":"Swift","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swift","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Equatable":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Equatable"}],"role":"symbol","title":"Equatable","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/equatable","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Equatable","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that can be compared for value equality."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Equatable"}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Hashable":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Hashable"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Hashable","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that can be hashed into a "},{"code":"Hasher","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to produce an integer hash value."}],"role":"symbol","title":"Hashable","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Hashable"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/hashable"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/choosing-between-structures-and-classes":{"title":"Choosing Between Structures and Classes","role":"article","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Decide how to store data and model behavior."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/choosing-between-structures-and-classes","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/choosing-between-structures-and-classes"}}}